A chord is 3 or more notes played together

A melody is them playing after each other

A chord is three or more notes played together to make a full sound

The C chord. 

Begin middle C with the thumb, skip one and add E, and then another and play G.

Number your fingers after a diagram, where 1 is your thumbs.

The chord will result in your hands being like a crab.

It gets easier over time if you play it for a while. Rest your hand and try again.

C is a root chord.

Play first. Ask questions later.


Play C Am F and G root chords. Your hands will be like a claw.

Your first rythm. Try playing notes an octave LOWER with left hand, and chords with right hand.

This is the 1950s Chord Progression.
